<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copelatus apicalis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Copelatus apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fairmaire, L" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="463 - 499" refId="B17" refString="Fairmaire, L, 1898. Materiaux pour la faune coleopterique de la region malgache. 7e note. . Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique 42: 463 - 499" title="Materiaux pour la faune coleopterique de la region malgache. 7 e note." volume="42" year="1898">Fairmaire (1898)</bibRefCitation>
from Suberbieville [=Maevatanana]. It is classified in the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copelatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Copelatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and currently placed in the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copelatus hydroporoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hydroporoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Copelatus hydroporoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="19" refId="B36">Guignot 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/03946975.1997.10539325" author="Nilsson, AN" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="11 - 48" refId="B56" refString="Nilsson, AN, Bilardo, A, Rocchi, S, 1997. A check list of Copelatus Erichson 1832 species (ColeopteraDytiscidae) from Afrotropical and Madagascan regions with a review of published penis drawings. . Tropical Zoology 10: 11 - 48" title="A check list of Copelatus Erichson 1832 species (ColeopteraDytiscidae) from Afrotropical and Madagascan regions with a review of published penis drawings." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/03946975.1997.10539325" volume="10" year="1997">Nilsson et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nilsson, AN" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" refId="B55" refString="Nilsson, AN, 2001. World catalogue of insects. Volume 3. Dytiscidae (Coleoptera). . Apollo Books, Stenstrup" title="World catalogue of insects. Volume 3. Dytiscidae (Coleoptera)." year="2001">Nilsson 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nilsson, AN" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" publicationUrl="http://www.waterbeetles.eu" refId="B57" refString="Nilsson, AN, Hajek, J, 2018. . http://www.waterbeetles.eu" url="http://www.waterbeetles.eu" year="2018">
Nilsson and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hájek">Hajek</normalizedToken>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). We have studied a male syntype of this species which was not found by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="19" refId="B36">Guignot (1961</bibRefCitation>
: note 638) and conclude that is not a 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copelatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Copelatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The syntype male has a stout spine-like setae on a protruding anterodistal corner of protarsomere IV which places it in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Madaglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madaglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Madaglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S1477200007002599" author="Shaverdo, HV" journalOrPublisher="Systematics and Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="43 - 51" refId="B69" refString="Shaverdo, HV, Monaghan, MT, Lees, DC, Ranaivosolo, R, Balke, M, 2008. Madaglymbus, a new genus of Malagasy endemic diving beetles and description of a highly unusual species based on morphology and DNA sequence data (Dytiscidae: Copelatinae). . Systematics and Biodiversity 6: 43 - 51" title="Madaglymbus, a new genus of Malagasy endemic diving beetles and description of a highly unusual species based on morphology and DNA sequence data (Dytiscidae: Copelatinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S1477200007002599" volume="6" year="2008">Shaverdo et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
) and we hereby transfer it to that genus: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Madaglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madaglymbus apicalis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Madaglymbus apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fairmaire, 1898) comb. nov.; in fact 
<bibRefCitation author="Gueorguiev, VB" journalOrPublisher="Izvestija na Zoologitjeskija Instituts Musei Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="5 - 45" refId="B25" refString="Gueorguiev, VB, 1968. Essai de classification des coleopteres Dytiscidae. I. Tribus Copelatini (Colymbetinae). . Izvestija na Zoologitjeskija Instituts Musei Sofia 28: 5 - 45" title="Essai de classification des coleopteres Dytiscidae. I. Tribus Copelatini (Colymbetinae)." volume="28" year="1968">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Guéorguiev">Gueorguiev</normalizedToken>
(1968
</bibRefCitation>
: 32) suggested it might belong to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Aglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Aglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Peut-être">&quot;Peut-etre</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="c’est">c'est</normalizedToken>
une 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Aglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Aglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
?&quot; [Eng. translation &quot;Maybe it is an 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Aglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Aglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;], which was correct since this was before 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Madaglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madaglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Madaglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erected for the Madagascar species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Aglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Aglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S1477200007002599" author="Shaverdo, HV" journalOrPublisher="Systematics and Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="43 - 51" refId="B69" refString="Shaverdo, HV, Monaghan, MT, Lees, DC, Ranaivosolo, R, Balke, M, 2008. Madaglymbus, a new genus of Malagasy endemic diving beetles and description of a highly unusual species based on morphology and DNA sequence data (Dytiscidae: Copelatinae). . Systematics and Biodiversity 6: 43 - 51" title="Madaglymbus, a new genus of Malagasy endemic diving beetles and description of a highly unusual species based on morphology and DNA sequence data (Dytiscidae: Copelatinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S1477200007002599" volume="6" year="2008">Shaverdo et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
